documentation.text:
@notice Allows an owner to delist their item if it's not currently rented.
 @param _itemId The ID of the item to delist.

devdoc.details: A smart contract for a decentralized item rental platform. Stores item details and IPFS metadata links on-chain. Handles rentals, returns, fees, and payments.

params._itemId: The ID of the item to delist.

getListedItemIds(uint256,uint256).details: Note: Iterating through all items on-chain can be inefficient for large lists. Consider events + off-chain indexing for production marketplaces.

params._limit: Maximum number of listed item IDs to return.
params._offset: Starting index for checking items (0 means check from item ID 1).

params._dailyRentalPrice: The rental price per day in Wei.
params._deposit: The security deposit required in Wei.
params._metadataCID: The IPFS Content ID linking to off-chain metadata (image, full desc, etc.).
params._title: The title or description of the item (basic).

rentItem(uint256).details: Requires payment equal to deposit + 1 day's rent.

params._itemId: The ID of the item to rent.

returnItem(uint256).details: Calculates rental fees, late fees, and distributes funds correctly.

params._itemId: The ID of the item to return.

devdoc.title: RentalPlatform

delistItem(uint256).notice: Allows an owner to delist their item if it's not currently rented.

getItem(uint256).notice: Get details for a specific item, including metadata CID.

getListedItemIds(uint256,uint256).notice: Get listed item IDs (example with basic pagination/limit).

listItem(string,uint256,uint256,string).notice: Allows an owner to list a new item for rent.

rentItem(uint256).notice: Allows a user to rent a listed item.

returnItem(uint256).notice: Allows the current renter to return an item.
